  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver employs tunable configuration parameters including base mesh edge length (0.15 mm near-wall), a power-law hemolysis model threshold shear stress (50 Pa), and a turbulence intensity inlet boundary value (5%). Validation results are reported at these chosen settings; however, no structured configuration node is bound to this package and the ContextOfUse does not constrain which parameter values must be used at deployment.",
