      "name": "Mesh convergence study — hemolysis index sensitivity",
      "description": "Three mesh refinement levels (coarse 0.30 mm, medium 0.20 mm, fine 0.15 mm base edge length) were evaluated. The fine mesh (0.15 mm) was selected as the production mesh based on GCI < 2% for the scalar hemolysis index. Results reported at the chosen mesh setting; the specific mesh size is referenced only in narrative text and is not captured in a linked configuration node."
    },
    {
