      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Power-law hemolysis model threshold calibration",
      "description": "The hemolysis power-law model was calibrated against Heuser-Opitz in-vitro data. A threshold shear stress of 50 Pa was identified as optimal, yielding RH predictions within 12% of experimental values across all 5 operating points. Validation metrics are reported at the chosen threshold setting; no structured parameter binding records this value for downstream deployment verification."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-03-turbulence-boundary",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Turbulence inlet boundary condition sensitivity",
      "description": "Inlet turbulence intensity was varied from 1% to 10%. A value of 5% was selected as representative of clinical cannula conditions and used in all production runs. Validation outcomes are reported at this chosen setting. The deployment specification does not constrain or verify this parameter value, creating a potential configuration gap between validated and deployed states."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-04-rh-acceptance",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index acceptance criterion check",
      "description": "Across all 5 flow-speed combinations, the computed relative hemolysis index RH ranged from 0.71 to 0.94, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Results were generated with the configuration parameters described in the model narrative (mesh 0.15 mm, threshold 50 Pa, turbulence 5%) but these values are not pinned in any structured field of this credibility package."
    }
