    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. The CFD model predicts relative hemolysis index within 12.3% of experimental values across all 5 operating conditions, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The credibility package is accepted as sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision for the Class II CPB device. Note: configuration parameters (mesh size 0.15 mm, hemolysis threshold 50 Pa, inlet turbulence intensity 5%) are documented in the model narrative and validation reports but are not captured in structured configuration bindings; the assessment team considers this acceptable at MRL 2 but recommends formalizing parameter pinning prior to any MRL 3 re-assessment.",
